    "gairishly" : "Same as Garish, Garishly, Garishness.",
    "engregge" : "To aggravate; to make worse; to lie heavy on. [Obs.] Chaucer.",
    "unguiculate" : "One of the Unguiculata.\n\n1. Furnished with nails, claws, or hooks; clawed. See the Note under Nail, n., 1. 2. (Bot.)  Furnished with a claw, or a narrow stalklike base, as the petals of a carnation.",
    "alalia" : "Inability to utter articulate sounds, due either to paralysis of the larynx or to that form of aphasia, called motor, or ataxis, aphasia, due to loss of control of the muscles of speech.",
