    "capriole" : "1. (Man.)  A leap that a horse makes with all fours, upwards only, without advancing, but with a kick or jerk of the hind legs when at the height of the leap. 2. A leap or caper, as in dancing. \"With lofty turns and caprioles.\" Sir J. Davies.\n\nTo perform a capriole. Carlyle.",
