    "colonitis" : "See Colitis.",
    "apotome" : "1. (Math.)  The difference between two quantities commensurable only in power, as between sq. root2 and 1, or between the diagonal and side of a square. 2. (Mus)  The remaining part of a whole tone after a smaller semitone has been deducted from it; a major semitone. [Obs.]",
    "nonchalant" : "Indifferent; careless; cool.",
    "sightful" : "Easily or clearly seen; distinctly visible; perspicuous. [Obs.] Testament of Love.",
